To use script.sub in a server you should execute with torque.
The patch.sh file is used to fix an error in lhpdf install on MG5_aMC_v2_5_2 version of MadGraph, to use it, you have to
define the bash variable MadGrapgSYS (path to the MadGraph folder) 

qsub script.sub

Also using nohub: (nohup myprogram > myprogram.out 2> myprogram.err)
nohup ./produccion-1.sh BackGround-mumuW_With0Jets.txt -Ne=50000 -Run=2 -Rc=/home/camilo/cms/Scripts_MadGraph_VLFTEO/Cards_Costumed/Wjet/run_card_CP5.dat -Delp=/home/camilo/cms/Scripts_MadGraph_VLFTEO/Cards_Costumed/Wjet/delphes_card.dat -Pyt=/home/camilo/cms/Scripts_MadGraph_VLFTEO/Cards_Costumed/Wjet/pythia8_card_CP5.dat > mumuW_With0Jets.out 2> mumuW_With0Jets.err &
To monitor use:
tail -f mumuW_With0Jets.out

